# React Component Template Rule

When generating a new React component, follow this layout:

```tsx
// /components/<Name>/<Name>.tsx
"use client";

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

export interface <Name>Props {
  label: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}

export default function <Name>({ label, onClick }: <Name>Props) {
  return (
    <section className={cn("p-4 text-foreground")} role="region">
      <button onClick={onClick}>{label}</button>
    </section>
  );
}
```

- Keep files short and focused.
- Separate logic into a hook: `/components/<Name>/use<Name>.ts`
- Create `/components/<Name>/index.ts` to export all parts.
- Create minimal test in `<Name>.test.tsx`.

